      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": true,
      "shortest": false,
      "solution": "#include <iostream>\n\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main()\n{\n    int width;\n    int height;\n    cin >> width >> height; cin.ignore();\n\n    int total = 0;\n    \n    for (int i = 0; i < height; i++) {\n        for (int j = 0; j < width; j++) {\n            int num;\n            cin >> num; cin.ignore();\n            if (i == 0          || j == 0 ||\n                i == height - 1 || j == width - 1\n            ) total += num;\n        }\n    }\n\n    cout << total << endl;\n}",
      "statement": "Given a 2D matrix of [[width]] × [[height]] integers [[num]], sum up all the integers on the perimeter of the matrix.",
